media:group.media:title: William the Bookkeeper
media:group.media:description:
This week Beau and Josh chat all about The Domesday Book, William the Conqueror’s extensive project to record practically all the property and resources in his kingdom. Was its purpose to calculate taxes and gelds, or was it more of an exercise in legitimising vast theft, or was it both?
